Female: Brachypterous, rarely macropterous; length 4.1–5.6. COLORATION: As in male. VESTITURE: As in male. STRUCTURE AND MESAUREMENTS: Body 2.2–2.6× as long as width of pronotum. Head: Frons without transverse striae, smooth or slightly rugose, head 1.2–1.3× wider than high; vertex 2.6–3.3× as wide as eye; antennal segment II 0.6–0.9× as long as basal width of pronotum, 0.9–1.3× as long as width of head. Thorax: Pronotum 1.9–2.3× as wide as long and 1.2–1.5× as wide as head, with concave posterior margin; hemelytra ranging in length from reaching anterior margin of abdominal segment IV to covering all abdomen, typically reaching abdominal segments VII or VIII; cuneus delimited by very short and shallow suture; claval commissure as long as inner claval margin; posterior and lateral margins rounded. GENITALIA: Dorsal labiate plate large, sclerotized rings large, triangular, with short and narrow sclerotized area adjacent to inner margin of each ring (fig. 14); posterior wall of bursa copulatrix with uniformly sclerotized trapeziform sclerite, incision on the anterior margin narrow and not reaching middle of sclerite, anterior angles smooth or slightly ribbed, not dentate; posterior margin with large sclerites at sides (fig. 18); vulva with pair of straight sclerites, not forming circle (as in fig. 19,
O. styx
).
